{"word":"μεμπτός","slug":"μεμπτός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μεμπτός</b></el> <el>(μεμπτός, ή, όν) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be blamed, blameworthy</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>μεμπτότερος</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <el>οὐ μ.</el> not <i>contemptible</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>μεμπτῶς</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>throwing blame upon</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; where <el>μεμπτός</el> is <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> for <el>-τή.</el><p/></div>"}]}